If on a longer walk - say one with a challenge of aiming for a certain number of steps also, achieving 3 or more brisk walks is easy for me. Some days - due to arthritis - my feet/legs hurt, so I try and gain at least 3, but happy if I get the one. For someone with severe arthritis (my daughter has RA very badly) she cannot walk briskly, so when I am out with her, we rarely achieve anything brisk - but we are out for at least 30 minutes minimum (more than we would have done) so happy.
